		{"id":"4bf3fd846eea4ebf","x":-140,"y":-4283,"width":1493,"height":5243,"type":"text","text":"Here is the updated and **fully aligned technical specification** reflecting the corrected system architecture, where the **Alexatron is a self-contained master controller** that the user accesses via SSH, and which controls both its own animatronics and external puppets.\n\n---\n\n# üß† Technical Specification: Alexatron-Based Puppet Control System\n\n**Project Module:** Controller Development  \n**Function:** Centralized gesture, voice, and servo control system for both the Alexatron and external puppets  \n**Version:** v1.1  \n**Last Updated:** 2025-06-17\n\n---\n\n## 1. üåê System Overview\n\nThe **Alexatron** functions as a self-contained master controller integrating:\n\n- Web UI for live dialogue and gesture input\n    \n- Chatterbox AI engine for real-time TTS and emotion parsing\n    \n- Vision processing for gesture recognition\n    \n- Servo Bus system to actuate internal and external animatronics\n    \n- Remote access via SSH for programming, monitoring, and control\n    \n\n---\n\n## 2. üß± System Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    Z[\"User SSH Access\"] --> A[\"Alexatron Master Controller\"]\n\n    subgraph Alexatron System\n        A1[\"Web UI + Dialogue Input\"]\n        A2[\"Chatterbox Engine\"]\n        A3[\"Alexatron Audio Output\"]\n        A4[\"Servo Bus Protocol\"]\n        A5[\"Face & Gesture Camera\"]\n        A6[\"Vision Engine: OpenCV + MediaPipe\"]\n        A7[\"Alexatron Animatronics\"]\n\n        A1 -->|Text/Speech| A2\n        A2 -->|TTS/Voice| A3\n        A2 -->|Servo Commands| A4\n        A5 -->|Landmarks| A6\n        A6 -->|Gesture Triggers| A4\n        A4 -->|Self-Control| A7\n    end\n\n    A -->|Puppet Commands| B[\"Secondary Puppet MCU\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. üéõ Subsystem Breakdown\n\n### 3.1. Remote User Access (SSH)\n\n- **Purpose:** Headless control, deployment, and debugging\n    \n- **Interface:** `ssh user@alexatron.local`\n    \n- **Tools:** VS Code Remote SSH, CLI gesture injector, log streaming\n    \n\n---\n\n### 3.2. Web UI + Dialogue Input\n\n- **Runs inside Alexatron**\n    \n- **Purpose:** Interface for typing dialogue, triggering gestures\n    \n- **Stack:** HTML/JS frontend, Python backend (Flask or FastAPI)\n    \n- **Functionality:**\n    \n    - Dialogue console\n        \n    - Servo macro buttons\n        \n    - Live voice injection\n        \n\n---\n\n### 3.3. Chatterbox Engine\n\n- **Runs on-device**\n    \n- **Functions:**\n    \n    - Converts typed/speech input into voice\n        \n    - Routes gestures based on intent/emotion\n        \n- **Extensible:** Can integrate GPT-4o or local LLM to enrich context mapping\n    \n- **Voice Output:** Routed to internal speaker system (TTS or recorded)\n    \n\n---\n\n### 3.4. Vision Engine + Camera\n\n- **Input:** USB or CSI camera module\n    \n- **Libraries:** OpenCV, MediaPipe\n    \n- **Purpose:** Detect facial orientation, hand gestures\n    \n- **Triggers:**\n    \n    - Wave ‚Üí `gesture_wave`\n        \n    - Look-at ‚Üí `look_towards_user`\n        \n    - Mouth open ‚Üí potential proxy for puppet speech trigger\n        \n\n---\n\n### 3.5. Servo Bus Protocol\n\n- **Purpose:** Routes commands to internal or external puppets\n    \n- **Message Format:**\n    \n\n```json\n{\n  \"target\": \"puppet_1\",\n  \"gesture\": \"nod_head\",\n  \"emotion\": \"neutral\",\n  \"duration_ms\": 600\n}\n```\n\n- **Internal Target:** `\"alexatron\"`\n    \n- **External Target:** `\"puppet_X\"` over serial/I2C/WiFi\n    \n\n---\n\n### 3.6. Alexatron Animatronics (Self-Control)\n\n- **Receives:** Servo gestures directly from bus\n    \n- **Function:** Move eyes, jaw, neck, etc.\n    \n- **Example Triggers:**\n    \n    - `eye_blink()`\n        \n    - `mouth_sync(\"Hello!\")`\n        \n\n---\n\n### 3.7. Secondary Puppet MCU\n\n- **Device:** Arduino Nano, ESP32, or Pi Pico\n    \n- **Connects to:** Alexatron via UART, I2C, or wireless\n    \n- **Function:** Execute received servo commands\n    \n- **Capabilities:**\n    \n    - Gesture macros\n        \n    - Optional TTS voice playback from file or onboard chip\n        \n\n---\n\n## 4. ‚öôÔ∏è Deployment and Execution Flow\n\n1. **SSH into Alexatron**\n    \n2. **Start system services** (`web_ui.py`, `chatterbox_server`, `vision_daemon`)\n    \n3. **Enter dialogue via Web UI** ‚Üí triggers Chatterbox\n    \n4. **Voice output plays** + emotion-mapped servo gestures executed\n    \n5. **Camera tracks motion**, gesture triggers routed to puppets\n    \n6. **Servo bus dispatches commands to Alexatron + secondary puppets**\n    \n\n---\n\n## 5. üß™ Test + Debug Tools\n\n|Tool|Purpose|\n|---|---|\n|`gesture_debug.py`|Manually inject gestures over bus|\n|`cam_debug.py`|Overlay face/hand tracking on live video|\n|`servo_scope.py`|Plot servo command timing/debug jitter|\n|Web UI Console|Visual interface for triggering macros and speech|\n\n---\n\n## 6. ‚úÖ MVP Targets\n\n-  Full on-device voice control with servo sync\n    \n-  Vision gesture detection to trigger puppet actions\n    \n-  External puppet control over serial\n    \n-  SSH access for remote dev and testing\n    \n-  Optional OBS overlay for livestream integration (future)\n    \n\n---\n\nWould you like a **deployment checklist**, a **YAML system manifest**, or a **hardware wiring map** next?"},
